==Etymology==
From Latin '''[[recursio]]''', ''[[running again]]'', from prefix '''[[re-]]''', ''again'', + '''[[cursio]]''', ''running'', from '''[[cursus]]''', perfect passive participle of '''[[currire]]''', ''[[run]]'', + noun of action suffix '''[[-io]]'''

==English==
==Noun==
'''recursion'''

#The act of [[recur]]ring.
#(''mathematics'') The act of defining a function partly in terms of that function itself.
#:''n! = n &times; (n - 1)! (for n > 0) or 1 (for n = 0) defines the factorial function using recursion.''
#(''computing'') The calling of a function from within that same function.
#:''This function uses recursion to compute factorials.''

